This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring May 15 as Peace Officers Memorial Day and May 9-15 as Police Week. The proclamation acknowledges the important role of law enforcement officers in maintaining peace and order in the country. It recognizes their bravery, dedication, and sacrifices, as they put their lives on the line to protect and serve their communities. The proclamation also highlights the support provided by the administration through grants to law enforcement agencies to ensure their safety and effectiveness. It calls upon all Americans to observe these events with appropriate ceremonies and activities and to reflect on the impact of peace officers in their lives.